<h3>genesis fund</h3><br>
a digital asset built with <a href="http://dogeparty.io">dogeparty</a> and funded with Bitcoin.
<hr>
<h11>SPECIFICATIONS:</h11><br>
<b><a href="http://dogepartychain.info/asset/BOGGS">dogepartychain.info/asset/BOGGS</a></b><p>
TOTAL SHARES:<h3>101</h3>
<hr>
Designed and built for the <a href="http://reimaginingwork.org">reimaginingwork.org</a> conference.<p>
<h1>&</h1>inspired by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grace_Lee_Boggs"><h3>Grace Lee Boggs</h3></a><br>
to benefit <a href="http://boggsschool.org/"><h5>BOGGS SCHOOL</h5></a>
<hr>
Once 1 BOGGScoin is equivalent to 2 Bitcoins in value, Boggscoin will burn one share and purchase a coin from coinmaker PLACEBO. This currency will be designed by the agency who inherits this BOGGS asset at the <a href="http://reimaginingwork.org">reimaginingwork.org</a> conference.<p>
<hr>
<h11>VISION:</h11><br>
BOGGScoin is a working proof of concept model for philanthropic fundraising using blockchain technologies. BOGGScoin is an economic art project founded in the "internet" principal of <i>open-source</i>.
<p>
BOGGScoin will be gifted to Grace Lee Boggs as an exchangeable asset that can be spent, transfered and allocated for upcoming projects.
<p>
Anyone can fund this asset to increase its value through a reserve built in Bitcoin. With a fixed supply, philanthropic funding can only increase the value of the coins being donated. Blockchains allow everyone to track the usage of their contributed coins. It is our intent that BOGGS inspire a philanthropic trend toward decentralized blockchain technologies.
<hr>
<h11>HOW TO FUND:</h11><br>
Send non refundable donations to the following addresses.

